              Belgacem Chariag
          
























































                    
                                                                        Belgacem Chariag
                                            
                                            

                            Chief Global Operations Officer

                        







































Belgacem Chariag is Chief Global Operations Officer for Baker Hughes, a GE company. Prior to his current role, Chariag served as President, Global Operations for Baker Hughes Incorporated. In this role, he led the company’s global operations organization, which is responsible for driving world-class operational performance, exceptional service and sales execution, as well as delivering strong operating profits throughout Baker Hughes’ footprint.
Previously, Chariag was Vice President and Chief Integration Officer for Baker Hughes, and before that he was President, Global Products and Services. He served as President of the company’s Eastern Hemisphere operations from 2009 until 2013.
Before joining Baker Hughes, Chariag was Vice President, Health, Safety, Environment, and Security for Schlumberger from January 2008 until January 2009. He also was President of the Well Services business line, and Marketing Vice President for Europe, Caspian, and Africa. Earlier in his career, Chariag held a variety of management positions for the company, including Managing Director in Egypt, East Africa, and the East Mediterranean and technical support and management positions in the US, Angola, Tunisia, the UAE and Qatar.
Chariag earned a Master of Business Administration degree in global energy from the University of Calgary and a Bachelor of Science degree in petroleum engineering from the University of Texas.




















