The Oil & Gas business ("GE O&G") of General Electric Company ("GE") entered into an offer letter and stay and win award letter with each of Derek Mathieson (Chief Commercial Officer for Baker Hughes Incorporated ("BHI")) and Belgacem Chariag (President, Global Operations for BHI) on June 1 and June 2, 2017, respectively, which set forth the terms on which the executive would be employed by Baker Hughes, a GE company ("BHGE"), following the closing of the proposed transactions (the "Transactions") to combine BHI with GE O&G. Each letter is contingent on the closing of the Transactions and ratification by the Board of Directors of BHGE, and each letter will become an obligation of BHGE on the closing of the Transactions.
